{"title":"TRed ASHAA wild aero, ergo track bar & prototype Peregrine Falcon track bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/30/tred-ashaa-wild-aero-ergo-track-bar-prototype-peregrine-falcon-track-bike/","date":1633029313000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;green front\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150519/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_front-end.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-273260\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>TRed’s ASHAA aero carbon track bar is the wildest, most niche handlebar we’ve ever seen. And their new Peregrine Falcon track bike is just as likely to make you faster!</p><p>Do you need this wild shapely new ASHAA carbon track bar? Probably not unless you are regularly in the velodrome, racing a wide range of track disciplines. But that’s not to say this niche, UK-made ergonomic carbon handlebar isn’t worth a closer look. Developed to provide all the possible hand positions a track rider could dream of, this dramatically-shaped, lightweight, and crazy expensive Ashaa track bar is already on its way to the next Olympics, and could shape road bars to come, as well…</p><h2>TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oE5TtdcoAGU?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Aerodynamic and ergonomic <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=aerodynamic+ergonomic+handlebar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">handlebars</a> are nothing new. We’ve even seen slippery <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2016/02/08/predator-circles-its-prey-with-new-the-major-track-one-piece-carbon-handlebar-stem/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">aero track bar+stem</a> combos and a set of bolt-on track <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/04/04/bfs2018-8bar-tmplhof-team-crit-bike-matching-team-kit-components/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">aero hoods</a>, but outside of that <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/01/coefficient-wave-rr-handlebar-give-you-an-ultra-aero-position-no-illegal-tuck-needed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Coefficient Wave</a> bar (<em>which the UCI said no to, apparently</em>), truly new handlebar shaping has been rare.</p><p>Now, TRed’s new Ashaa bar hopes to give track racers a better grip.</p><h3>Aero, Ergo Development</h3><div id=\"attachment_273272\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273272\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;track testing\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150515/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_Barcelona-velodrome-hand-positions-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273272\">all photos c. TRed</p></div><p>Developed by Romolo Stanco, the engineering brains behind TRed bike designs and their TOOT line of components, the Ashaa bar is built to offer support &amp; control in a wider range of hand positions as seen in endurance track racing. Just like we know road racers like to assume odd positions to get more aero (<em>because the UCI banned most of them</em>), track racers do the same.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;angled rear\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150510/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-bar-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>Ashaa brings shapely hoods and sharp finger grips to the track, flat horizontal drops to get low, and generous flare to make room for racers’ wrists.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;Barcelona velodrome testing\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150506/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_track-testing-Barcelona-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>TRed debuted the new aero, ergo bar with their factory racing team at the Velodrom d’Horta in Barcelona as a proof-of-concept – in addition to the team’s prototype Peregrine Falcon track bikes. Because it’s easy to develop ergonomics in CFD and the wind tunnel, but it’s another thing to see if those new hand positions really offer the grip and control while racing from a dead stop, and then blasting around a wooden track at 60km/hr.</p><p>Barcelona seemed a fitting stop as the home of the 1992 Olympics (and Boardman’s controversial aero positioning), as the team have their sights set on performing at the upcoming Paris 2024 Olympics.</p><h3>Tech details, pricing &amp; availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;angled\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150501/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_angled-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>What started as a hand-drawn sketch, then 3D-printed mockup, has now been handcrafted in carbon in Great Britain by CarbonWasp in a version you can buy now.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;dimensions\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions-297x149.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions-800x400.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions-120x60.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150457/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_dimensions-1536x768.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>The UK-made endurance track handlebar sells for 799€ in a single size, with 93mm drop &amp; 108mm reach. The bar is just 28cm wide (center-center) at the virtual hoods. And with 20° of flare to the drops, it measures out to 37cm wide at the horizontal drops (c-c). The monocoque carbon TRed TOOT Ashaa track bar is designed with a 31.8mm clamp to fit conventional stems.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top.jpg\" alt=\"TRed TOOT ASHAA ergonomic carbon track handlebar,&nbsp;top\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150454/TRed-TOOT-Asha-aerodynamic-ergonomic-carbon-track-handlebar_top-768x432.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>While the Ashaa track bar is certainly niche, TRed admits that this project is a proving ground that they expect to adapt to the road. So, expect to see a similar blend of lightweight aerodynamics and ergonomics coming soon in a new TRed Ashaa road handlebar too…</p><p><a href=\"http://www.tootengineering.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>TOOTengineering.com</em></a></p><h3>TRed Peregrine Falcon prototype track bike</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side.jpg\" alt=\"TRed Peregrine Falcon prototype track bike\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150451/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_side-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>As for the prototype TRed track bikes… Named the Peregrine Falcon, it’s a far evolution of their Mania platform, a long-running project to build a faster bike for Giairo Ermeti’s run at the Italian track championship title. Details remain thin on the likely alloy race bike, but we can extrapolate out a number of features…</p><div id=\"attachment_273274\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273274\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit.jpg\" alt=\"TRed Peregrine Falcon prototype track bike, Francesca Selva pursuit\" width=\"1650\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit.jpg 1650w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit-297x144.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit-800x388.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit-120x58.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit-768x372.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150523/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-pursuit-1536x745.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1650px) 100vw, 1650px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273274\">c. Francesca Selva</p></div><p>The huge carbon fork with a shroud/cowl in front of the frame’s headtube is an obvious move to smooth airflow over the front of the bike, but since it doesn’t appear to connect back to the upper headset cup it’s clearly not of the ‘external steerer’ variety.</p><div id=\"attachment_273275\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273275\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint.jpg\" alt=\"TRed Peregrine Falcon prototype track bike, Francesca Selva sprint\" width=\"1500\" height=\"720\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint-297x143.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint-800x384.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint-120x58.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150527/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_Ashaa-track-bar_Francesca-Selva-sprint-768x369.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273275\">c. Francesca Selva</p></div><p>This prototype suggests a transition from the fork crown into the massive aero downtube, but they don’t seem to quite match up yet, suggesting there’s more refinement ahead for the final integrated frameset.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar.jpg\" alt=\"TRed Peregrine Falcon prototype track bike, stem detail\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/30150446/TRed-Peregrine-Falcon-prototype-track-bike_front-end-with-Ashaa-aero-track-bar-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>The Peregrine Falcon does also get a dropped stem that finishes just above the top of the toptube – making room for a weld, but also allowing varied handlebar setups depending on race discipline. Out back, a relatively small section integrated seatmast appears to be topped out by a conventional seatpost that may slide down into the mast. It looks like the bike gets a T47 threaded bottom bracket, and long track ends with stainless steel faces.</p><p><a href=\"http://tredbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>TRedBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5cdd6e1f993f601648eceece9b5f6e7cac3cc331b378e987d1e42f7532fad550","category":"Cycling"}